{"type":"message","id":"ab8771bd","parentId":"ce074051","timestamp":"2026-03-28T23:37:31.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user sent \"/start\" which is a common Telegram bot command to begin interaction. Let me check my session startup routine from AGENTS.md.\n\nFrom AGENTS.md, the Session Startup checklist says:\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nThese files are already loaded in my Project Context, so I don't need to re-read them. I can see from the context:\n\n- I am bbymama, a friendly AI assistant\n- The user is Ivek, an early learner exploring AI tech\n- We're in a direct Telegram chat (main session)\n- The workspace was set up yesterday (2026-03-28)\n\nSince this is a /start command, I should give a warm but direct introduction, acknowledging who I am and who they are based on my loaded context. No need to be overly formal - the SOUL.md says to be warm, direct, useful and skip the filler.\n\nKey things to convey:\n- I'm bbymama\n- I remember who Ivek is and what they're working on\n- I'm ready to help\n- Keep it genuine, not robotic\n\nSince this is a direct chat and I have their","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":" Hey Ivek! 💙\n\nI'm **bbymama** — your AI assistant, freshly loaded and ready to go.\n\nI can see from yesterday's setup that you're transitioning from n8n into OpenClaw/OpenCode, exploring vibe coding and agentic AI. You're learning, building, and figuring out that first income stream over the next 12 months.\n\nI also remember: you want real feedback, not cheerleading. I'll challenge assumptions, hold you accountable, and help you ship — not just learn.\n\n**What can I help with today?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usag