Type: heading_2\n   Heading 2: 📅 Daily...\n4. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Focus Block (2-4h) — One deep work session...\n5. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Learn by Doing — Build, don't watch...\n6. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Capture Insights — Log in memory/...\n7. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Review Alignment — On track for 12-mo goal?...\n8. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ No Shiny Objects — Finish current project first...\n9. Type: divider\n   Divider\n10. Type: heading_2\n   Heading 2: 📆 Monthly...\n11. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Ship 1 Project — MVP counts...\n12. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Skill Deep Dive — Master 1 tool...\n13. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Income Brainstorm — 3-5 ideas, pick 1...\n14. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Review & Purge — Drop stalled projects...\n15. Type: divider\n   Divider\n16. Type: heading_2\n   Heading 2: 🎯 Yearly (12-Month)...\n17. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ 1st Income Stream — $1+ from AI/automation...\n18. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Portfolio — 3-5 shipped projects...\n19. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Foundation — Coding fundamentals solid...\n20. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Audience — Build in public...\n21. Type: to_do\n   Todo: ⬜ Self-Trust — Prove you can follow through...\n\n=== End of Blocks ===\n\nPage Title: To-do list","cwd":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774742358320}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3f9ef63","parentId":"d35383bf","timestamp":"2026-03-29T00:00:09.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great! I can see your todo list structure. It's actually pretty well organized already with headings and dividers. Now I can add some visual enhancements. Here's what I'll do:\n\n**Visual Improvements Plan:**\n1. **Add a cover image** (abstract gradient or minimal)\n2. **Add an icon** (maybe 🎯 or 📊)\n3. **Add callouts** for motivation/reminders\n4. **Add a progress section** at the top\n5. **Add colors** to some text\n6. **Maybe add a simple database view** for the todo items\n\nLet me start by trying to update the page with some visual elements. First, I'll try to add a callout block for motivation.\n\nLet me write a Python script to add visual"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_854d16f0bd86474697c96e5f","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/add_visuals.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport os\nimport requests\nimport json\n\n# Get Notion API key from environment\nNOTION_KEY = \"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\"\nPAGE_ID = \"331996240a6680268f4bc68282b2bba6\"\n\nheaders = {\n    \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {NOTION_KEY}\",\n    \"Notion-Version\": \"2022-06-28\",\n    \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n}\n\n# First, let's add a callout block right after the title\ncallout_data = {\n    \"children\": [\n        {\n            \"object\": \"block\",\n            \"type\": \"callout\",\n            \"callout\": {\n                \"rich_text\": [\n                    {\n                        \"type\": \"text\",\n                        \"text\": {\n                            \"content\": \"Remember: You're building momentum, not chasing perfection. Small consistent steps beat big sporadic leaps. \"\n                        }\n                    }\n                ],\n                \"icon\": {\n                    \"emoji\": \"💙\"\n                },\n                \"color\": \"blue_background\"\n            }\n        }\n    ]\n}\n\n# Add the callout after the first block (heading_1)\nprint(\"Adding motivational callout...\")\ntry:\n    url = f\"https://api.notion.com/v1/blocks/{PAGE_ID}/children\"\n    response = requests.patch(url, headers=headers, json=callout_data)\n    \n    if response.status_code == 200:\n        print(\"✅ Added callout successfully!\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"❌ Failed to add callout: {response.status_code}\")\n        print(response.text)\n        \nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n\n# Now let's add a simple divider before the daily section\nprint(\"\\nAdding visual divider before daily section...\")\ntry:\n    # Get current blocks to find where to insert\n    url = f\"https://api.notion.com/v1/blocks/{PAGE_ID}/children\"\n    response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)\n    blocks = response.json().get('results', [])\n    \n    # Find the index of \"📅 Daily\" heading (should be after heading_1 and callout)\n    daily_index = None\n    for i, block in enumerate(blocks):\n        if block.get('type') == 'heading_2':\n            text = block.get('heading_2', {}).get('rich_text', [])\n            if text and text[0].get('plain_text', '').startswith('📅 Daily'):\n                daily_index = i\n                break\n    \n    if daily_index is not None:\n        # We'll add a colorful quote before the daily section\n        quote_data = {\n            \"children\": [\n                {\n                    \"object\": \"block\",\n                    \"type\": \"quote\",\n                    \"quote\": {\n                        \"rich_text\": [\n                            {\n                                \"type\": \"text\",\n                                \"text\": {\n                                    \"content\": \"Today is a fresh start. What one thing will you complete?\",\n                                    \"link\": None\n                                },\n                                \"annotations\": {\n                                    \"bold\": True,\n                                    \"italic\": False,\n                                    \"strikethrough\": False,\n                                    \"underline\": False,\n                                    \"code\": False,\n                                    \"color\": \"purple\"\n                                }\n                            }\n                        ],\n                        \"color\": \"purple_background\"\n                    }\n                }\n            ]\n        }\n        \n        # Insert before the daily heading\n        insert_url = f\"https://api.notion.com/v1/blocks/{PAGE_ID}/children\"\n        # Note: For inserting at a specific position, we need to use the after parameter\n        # But PATCH endpoint doesn't support insert positions, so we need to append and rearrange\n        # For now, let's append and update later\n        \n        print(\"Would insert quote before daily section (requires block repositioning API)\")\n        \nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n\nprint(\"\\nDone!\")"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774742358322,"responseId":"e7f2c5f62c4943f2985a3e90e7033e1d"}}
