{"type":"message","id":"2f78f2f2","parentId":"bbeafd5c","timestamp":"2026-03-29T00:03:13.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, I see the issue - the new blocks got appended at the end instead of after the heading. That's how the Notion API works with PATCH. Let me add one more visual element - a toggle list for \"Today's focus\" that can expand to show details.\n\nActually, before I add more, let me check: do you want me to continue adding more visual elements? I've already added:\n\n1. ✅ **Blue callout** with motivation\n2. ✅ **Progress tracker** (visual bar + percentage)\n3. ✅ **Orange color** to yearly goals heading\n\n**What else would you like?**\n- Toggle lists for task details\n- More color coding (priority levels)\n- Icons for each todo item\n- A quote section\n- Background colors for sections\n- Better organization (like columns)?\n\nAlso, I should fix the ordering - the new elements are at the bottom. To fix that, I'd need to use Notion's \"reorder children\" endpoint or just manually drag them in your Notion interface (probably easier).\n\nWant me to add anything specific or should we call it good?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774742570891,"responseId":"ce269c5cc4de4524b8b0178ce3cf442f"}}
