{"type":"message","id":"1e21932f","parentId":"a8f06d88","timestamp":"2026-03-29T00:10:49.091Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's what I've added to make your Notion todo list visually appealing:\n\n## ✅ **Visual Upgrades Applied**\n\n### **1. Color-Coded Sections**\n- 📅 **Daily Goals** → Green\n- 📆 **Monthly Goals** → Blue  \n- 🎯 **Yearly Goals** → Orange\n\n### **2. Custom Icons for Each Task**\n- Every todo now has a relevant emoji (🎯🔨📝🔍🚫🚀🧠💰🧹💸📁🏗️👥💪)\n- Makes scanning easier and more engaging\n\n### **3. Interactive Elements**\n- **Today's Focus Toggle** → Green background with collapsible tips\n- **Motivational Callout** → Blue background with 💙 icon\n- **Visual Key** → Shows priority color meanings\n\n### **4. Progress Tracking**\n- **Progress bar** (▰▰▰▰▰▰▰▰▰▰▱▱▱▱) with 70% placeholder\n- Instructions to update daily\n\n### **5. Clean Finishing**\n- Decorative dividers\n- Completion message at bottom\n\n## **🎨 Result:** \nYour todo list went from functional text to a **visually engaging, color-coded system** that's easier to navigate and more motivating to use.\n\n**Note:** The new elements appear at the bottom in the API view, but in Notion UI they should appear in logical positions. You might want to **drag the new blocks** (callout, progress tracker, toggle, key) up to sit right after your main heading for better flow.\n\nWant me to add anything else? Maybe a cover image or page icon?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774743016612,"responseId":"a6a6244e4a8b46b2a44f9838a17b6af6"}}
